name: js/Collections/BaseCollection.js
BaseCollection
description:
Subclass of Backbone.Collection.

Some functionality of Backbone.Collection is overridden to facilitate server-based pagination, filtering, and sorting.

name: getEnumerations
description:
Returns enumerations of this Collection. These are custom-defined in the subclasses.

Enumerations should be defined in subclasses as follows:
- [{field: string, label: string, values: [{value: primitive type, label: string}] (optional)}]

In the above:
- "field" is a property of the associated Model in the Collection
- "label" is a string that will appear in the table header
- "values" is optional; populate this array with explicit "value"/"label"s if desired, else BaseCollection will determine the values for enumeration based on the contents of the Collection
todo: Rodan server should provide explicit enumerations

name: parseIdFromUrl
todo: this should be moved to a utility class

name: fetch
description:
Override of fetch to allow for generic handling.

Note that we save the data options. This is in case we do a create
and have to reload/fetch the previous collection. We need to preserve
the fetch parameters.

name: create
description:
Override of create.

This override exists because we do NOT want to add it to the collection
by default (as there's a limit to what the server returns for collections,
and we need to respect that). However, if the save worked, we do want to do a fetch
to update the Collection. The fetch is called in the custom success handler for creation.

There's also the case if this Collection is local and not associated with a DB Collection.

return.description: instance of Backbone.Model or subclass of Backbone.Model

name: fetchSort
description:
Requests a sorted fetch. This is not called "sort" because backbone already has
a sort method for the Collection.

If no options.data is passed, the options.data from the last fetch are used.

params.name: ascending
params.description: results will return in ascending order iff true

params.name: field
params.description: name of field to sort by

name: fetchFilter
description:
Requests a filtered fetch.

If no options.data is passed, the options.data from the last fetch are used.

params.name: filters
params.description: array of objects; {name: string, value: primitive}; what filters can be used is defined in Rodan

name: fetchPage
description:
Requests a page to be fetched.

If no options.data is passed, the options.data from the last fetch are used.

params.name: page
params.description: non-negative page number to retrieve from server

name: getPagination
description: Returns pagination object for this Collection.
todo: point to pagination info on Rodan server

name: url
description: Returns the URL associated with this Collection.

name: syncCollection
description: Syncs the Collection while preserving the last used fetch options.data.

description: Handles a succesful creation. All this does is "properly" reload the collection.

name: _attemptWorkflowRunCreation
description:
Check WorkflowRun Resource assignments.

This method checks if any Resource assignments are ResourceLists.
If there are and the ResourceList has no ID, it saves the list and waits for a response.
If it has an ID, it replaces the object with the URL for that ResourceList.
If a reference is just to an array of REsource refs, it is ignored.

If everything checks out create the WorkflowRun and return true. Else return false.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOW_SAVED
description: Triggered when Workflow has been saved. Sends {workflow: Workflow}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOW_SELECTED
description: Triggered when the user selects an individual Workflow. Sends {workflow: Workflow}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOW_SELECTED_COLLECTION
description: Triggered when the user selects to see all available Workflows. Sends {project: Project (Project associated with WorkflowCollection)}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOW_CREATE
description: Request a Workflow be created. Takes {project: Project}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOW_DELETE
description: Request a Workflow be deleted. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOW_EXPORT
description: Request a Workflow be exported. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOW_IMPORT
description: Request a Workflow be imported. Takes {}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOW_SAVE
description: Request a Workflow be saved/updated. Takes {workflow: Workflow, fields: {object with attributes to change}}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SELECTED
description: Triggered when the user selects an individual Workflow to edit. Sends {workflow: Workflow}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWBUILDER_LOADED_WORKFLOW
description: Triggered when a Workflow is loaded into the WorkflowBuilder. Sends {workflow: Workflow}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWBUILDER_VALIDATED_WORKFLOW
description: Triggered when a Workflow has been validated. Sends {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ADD_CONNECTION
description: Request a Connection be added to a Workflow between two ports. Takes {inputport: InputPort, outputport: OutputPort, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ADD_DISTRIBUTOR
description: Request a WorkflowJob be created from a Job of category Configuration.RESOURCE_DISTRIBUTOR_CATEGORY that can satisfy the provided InputPorts. Takes {inputports: [InputPort], workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ADD_INPUTPORT
description: Request an InputPort be added to a WorkflowJob. Takes {inputporttype: InputPortType, workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ADD_OUTPUTPORT
description: Request an OutputPort be added to a WorkflowJob. Takes {outputporttype: InputPortType, workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow, targetinputports: [InputPort] (optional)}. If targetinputports is provided the WorkflowBuilder will attempt to create Connections between the created OutputPort and those InputPort.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ADD_WORKFLOWJOB
description: Request a WorkflowJob be created from a Job. Takes {job: Job, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ADD_WORKFLOWJOBGROUP
description: Request a WorkflowJobGroup be created for the provided WorkflowJobs. Takes {workflowjobs: [WorkflowJob], workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_ASSIGN_RESOURCE
description: Request a Resource be assigned to an InputPort. Takes {resource: Resource, inputport: InputPort, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_CREATE_WORKFLOWRUN
description: Request a WorkflowRun be created. The WorkflowBuilder will use the known Resource assignments that have been made. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_GET_RESOURCEASSIGNMENTS
description: Request the Resources that are currently assigned to an InputPort. Takes {inputport: InputPort}. Returns [Resource].

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_GET_SATISFYING_INPUTPORTS
description: Request all InputPorts that could satisfy the provided OutputPort in the given Workflow. Takes {workflow: Workflow, outputport: OutputPort}. Returns [string] (InputPort URLs).

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_IMPORT_WORKFLOW
description: Request a Workflow (origin) be added to another Workflow (target). Takes {origin: Workflow, target: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_LOAD_WORKFLOW
description: Request a Workflow be fetched and loaded. If no Workflow has yet been loaded in the WorkflowBuilder, or the Workflow to be loaded differs from the one currently loaded in the WorkflowBuilder, the WorkflowBuilder will be initialized with the new Workflow. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_REMOVE_CONNECTION
description: Request a Connection be removed from a Workflow. Takes {connection: Connection, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_REMOVE_INPUTPORT
description: Request an InputPort be removed from a WorkflowJob. Takes {inputport: InputPort, workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_REMOVE_OUTPUTPORT
description: Request an OutputPort be removed from a WorkflowJob. Takes {outputport: OutputPort, workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_REMOVE_WORKFLOWJOB
description: Request a WorkflowJob be removed from a Workflow. Takes {workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_REMOVE_WORKFLOWJOBGROUP
description: Request a WorkflowJobGroup and all its associated WorkflowJobs be removed from a Workflow. Takes {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SET_ADDPORTS
description: Request that future WorkflowJob creation automatically adds minimal ports. Takes {addports: boolean}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_JOBCOLLECTION_VIEW
description: Request a Job collection view be displayed for adding Jobs to the currently loaded Workflow. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_RESOURCEASSIGNMENT_VIEW
description: Request a resource assignment view be displayed for an InputPort. Takes {inputport: InputPort, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_WORKFLOW_VIEW
description: Request a Workflow data view be displayed for a Workflow. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_WORKFLOWCOLLECTION_VIEW
description: Request a Workflow collection view be displayed for importing Workflows. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_WORKFLOWJOB_PORTS_VIEW
description: Request a port view for adding/deleting ports for a WorkflowJob be displayed. Takes {workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_WORKFLOWJOB_SETTINGS_VIEW
description: Request a WorkflowJob settings view be displayed for a WorkflowJob. Takes {workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_WORKFLOWJOB_VIEW
description: Request a WorkflowJob data view be displayed for a WorkflowJob. Takes {workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_SHOW_WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_VIEW
description: Request a WorkflowJobGroup data view be displayed for a WorkflowJobGroup. Takes {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_UNASSIGN_RESOURCE
description: Request a Resource be unassigned to an InputPort. Takes {resource: Resource, inputport: InputPort, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_UNGROUP_WORKFLOWJOBGROUP
description: Request a WorkflowJobGroup be removed from a Workflow, but keep all associated WorkflowJobs, ports, and Connections. Takes {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup, workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWBUILDER_VALIDATE_WORKFLOW
description: Request a Workflow be validated. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWJOB_CREATED
description: Triggered when WorkflowJob created. Sends {workflowjob: WorkflowJob}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWJOB_DELETED
description: Triggered when WorkflowJob deleted. Sends {workflowjob: WorkflowJob}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWJOB_SAVED
description: Triggered when WorkflowJob saved. Sends {workflowjob: WorkflowJob}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOB_CREATE
description: Request a WorkflowJob be created of a Job type and added to a Workflow. Takes {job: Job, workflow: Workflow, addports: boolean, targetinputports: [InputPort] (optional)}. The minimum required InputPorts will be created iff addports is true. If targetinputports array of InputPorts is provided, Connections will be made to those InputPorts (from this WorkflowJob's OutputPort) iff the WorkflowJob created has one and only one OutputPort.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOB_DELETE
description: Request a WorkflowJob be deleted. Takes {workflowjob: WorkflowJob}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOB_SAVE
description: Request a WorkflowJob be saved/updated. Takes {workflowjob: WorkflowJob, workflow: Workflow (optional)}. If a Workflow is passed the WorkflowJobController will request a validation for that Workflow after the save has completed.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_IMPORTED
description: Triggered when WorkflowJobGroup imported. Sends {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_DELETED
description: Triggered when WorkflowJobGroup has been deleted. Sends {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_SAVED
description: Triggered when WorkflowJobGroup saved. Sends {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_DELETE
description: Request a WorkflowJobGroup be deleted. Takes {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_GET_PORTS
description: Request arrays of InputPort URLs and OutputPort URLs for the given WorkflowJobGroup. Takes {url: string (WorkflowJobGroup URL), workflow: Workflow}. Returns {inputports: [InputPort], outputports: [OutputPort]}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_IMPORT
description: Request a Workflow (origin) be imported into another Workflow (target) as a WorkflowJobGroup. Takes {target: Workflow, origin: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_LOAD_COLLECTION
description: Request WorkflowJobGroups be loaded for a given Workflow. Takes {workflow: Workflow}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWJOBGROUP_SAVE
description: Request a WorkflowJobGroup be saved/updated. Takes {workflowjobgroup: WorkflowJobGroup}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWRUN_CREATED
description: Triggered when WorkflowRun created. Sends {workflowrun: WorkflowRun}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWRUN_DELETED
description: Triggered when WorkflowRun deleted. Sends {workflowrun: WorkflowRun}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWRUN_SAVED
description: Triggered when WorkflowRun saved. Sends {workflowrun: WorkflowRun}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWRUN_SELECTED
description: Triggered when the user selects an individual WorkflowRun. Sends {workflow: WorkflowRun}.

name: EVENT__WORKFLOWRUN_SELECTED_COLLECTION
description: Triggered when the user selects to see all available WorkflowRuns. Sends {project: Project (Project associated with WorkflowRunCollection)}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWRUN_CREATE
description: Request a WorkflowRun be created. Takes {workflow: Workflow, assignments: [string (Resource URLs or individual ResourceList URL)] (index by InputPort URLs)}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWRUN_DELETE
description: Request a WorkflowRun be deleted. Takes {workflowrun: WorkflowRun}.

name: REQUEST__WORKFLOWRUN_SAVE
description: Request a WorkflowRun be saved/updated. Takes {model: WorkflowRun}.
